gov.sandia.cognition.hash

Interface HashFunction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, CloneableSerializable, Evaluator<byte[],byte[]>, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractHashFunction, Eva32Hash, Eva64Hash, FNV1a32Hash, FNV1a64Hash, MD5Hash, Murmur32Hash, Prime32Hash, Prime64Hash, SHA1Hash, SHA256Hash, SHA512Hash

    public interface HashFunction
extends CloneableSerializable, Evaluator<byte[],byte[]>
    A hash function maps an arbitrarily large input and maps it onto a finite-length output.
    Since:
    3.4.2
    Author:
    Kevin R. Dixon
